# How to setup mail.domainname.com for webmail in cPanel


The default webmail redirect on linux account is http://domainname.com/webmail. In order to change that default webmail redirect to mail.domainname.com, please do the following steps:

1) Please login to your cPanel and then click on Advanced DNS Zone Editor.

2) Then delete the current DNS entry for mail.domainname.com on  Zone File Records.

```diagram

```

3)once this is done, please click on Subdomains section in the cPanel and create a subdomain like mail.domainname.com.


```diagram

```

4) Once the sub-domain is created, you will see it listed at the bottom of the same page and then click on the Manage Redirection button. On the subdomain redirection window enter http://domainname.com/webmmail.com and then save it.

